  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "AUDIO OUTPUT NOTES (v1.1):\n\n1) MAX98357A I2S Class-D:\n   BCLK=IO18, LRCK=IO19, DIN=AMP_I2S_DOUT (separate I2S port from ES7243E)\n   SD_MODE = AMP_SD (IO33): HIGH=left ch play, LOW=shutdown, FLOAT=mono mix\n   Firmware: set LOW when BT connected, HIGH when disconnected\n\n2) PVDD power path:\n   VBAT → FB1(220Ω@100MHz ferrite, 0402) → C35(22uF 0805) → PVDD_FILT\n   → C22(10uF 0805) + C21(100nF 0402) → U4 PVDD\n   [FIXED] FB1 isolates 300kHz Class-D switching noise from VBAT/BQ24075\n\n3) BTL output filter (mandatory for Class-D):\n   L3/L4 = 10µH 0603, C23/C24 = 100nF 0402 to GND\n   DO NOT connect OUT+/OUT- to GND directly\n\n4) Headphone AC coupling:\n   [FIXED] C_HP_L/R: 100uF electrolytic 4x5.4mm → 47uF/10V X5R 0805 ceramic\n   Benefits: no polarity, smaller, longer life, lower ESR\n   fc = 1/(2pi × 600 × 47u) = 5.6Hz (sufficient for audio)\n\n5) BT Status LED:\n   [FIXED] IO34 is input-only on ESP32 → moved to IO32\n   IO32 was AUDIO_MUTE; SI4732 mute now controlled via I2C (property 0x0102)\n   LED: Blue 0603, R14=100R → ~22mA @ 3.3V (Vf≈1.1V)\n\n[FIX LOG v1.1 - 2026-04-28]\n  BUG-03: BT_LED on IO34 (input-only) → LED cannot light up\n  FIX-03: Reassigned to IO32; SI4732 MUTE via I2C instead of dedicated GPIO\n  BUG-04: No PVDD noise isolation → Class-D switching contaminates VBAT\n  FIX-04: Added FB1 ferrite bead 220R@100MHz 0402 + C35 22uF 0805\n  BUG-05: C_HP_L/R 100uF electrolytic (4x5.4mm, large, polarised)\n  FIX-05: Replaced with 47uF/10V X5R 0805 ceramic (2x1.25mm)"
    (at 210 90)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
